oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Two photographs of six and 3/4 lb. rainbow trout caught in Clinch River, Tenn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Two black and white photographs of a six and 3/4 lb. rainbow trout caught by Paul Newlin of Norris, Tennessee in the Clinch River below Norris Dam. First picture is Paul Newlin holding fish with a man, street front and automobiles in background. Newlin and other man are wearing hats and suits. In second photograph, two children (young girl and toddler boy) are looking at fish, with girl holding the fish. Sidewalk and store window are in background.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
